        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Does the patch make `system('command arg1 arg2 arg3')` behave similar to `system([&shell, split(&shellcmdflags), 'command', 'arg1', 'arg2', 'arg3'])`?\r\n\r\n`&shell` is not split so that when the list is collapsed to a string, the shell is escaped.\r\n\r\nIn `:h shell`, I don't understand the following example:\r\n```vim\r\nlet &shell='\"C:\\Program Files\\unix\\sh.exe\" -f'\r\n```\r\nWhat does `-f` do and why is it set on `shell`?",
            "created_at": "2018-01-13T16:47:23Z",
