        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Regarding your first question: yes, in its current state this patch does that.\r\n\r\nHowever, this breaks the behavior that you cite in your second question.  The specific example you provided would still work, but something like\r\n\r\n```vim\r\nlet &shell=/bin/bash\\ -f\r\n```\r\nwould no longer work.  The `-f` flag should really be a part of the `shellcmdflag` option instead of `shell`, but I don't think it's desirable to break this behavior.  I'm currently working to get around this issue.",
            "created_at": "2018-01-13T21:25:10Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/7846#issuecomment-357468393",
