        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "It does seem silly that we were tokenizing `p_sh`. \r\n\r\nOn the other hand, #4504 explicitly added support for crazy stuff like `set shell='shell-test -t jeff'`. Curious that the tests added there don't fail after your change.\r\n\r\nOne test does fail though:\r\n\r\n```\r\n[1m\u001b[35m[  FAILED  ]\u001b[0m\u001b[0m \u001b[36m./test/unit/helpers.lua\u001b[0m @ \u001b[36m764\u001b[0m: \u001b[1mshell functions shell_build_argv splits and unquotes &shell and &shellcmdflag\u001b[0m\r\n./test/unit/helpers.lua:731: (string) '\r\n...e/travis/build/neovim/neovim/test/unit/os/shell_spec.lua:102: Expected objects to be the same.\r\nPassed in:\r\n(table) {\r\n *[1] = '/Program\" \"Files/zsh -f'\r\n  [2] = 'ghi  jkl'\r\n  [3] = '-x'\r\n  [4] = '-o'\r\n  [5] = 'sh word split'\r\n  [6] = '-c'\r\n  [7] = 'abc  def' }\r\nExpected:\r\n(table) {\r\n *[1] = '/Program Files/zsh'\r\n  [2] = '-f'\r\n  [3] = 'ghi  jkl'\r\n  [4] = '-x'\r\n  [5] = '-o'\r\n  [6] = 'sh word split'\r\n  [7] = '-c'\r\n  [8] = 'abc  def' }'\r\n\r\nstack traceback:\r\n\t./test/unit/helpers.lua:747: in function 'itp_parent'\r\n```\r\n\r\nSo clearly this was an intentional behavior and the question is why.",
            "created_at": "2018-01-14T11:27:46Z",
