        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "The user cannot pass additional arguments to `&shell` when running `:terminal` so they have to use `termopen`. #4504 resolves that but breaks https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/7810 which is worse. The fix should have been to support passing arguments to `&shell` on `:terminal` instead of changing the handling of shell.\r\n\r\nI assume the test case is for Unix only so the actual result looks correct to me.",
